8. TAR File Generation & Sending

The generated XML is packaged into a .tar file.

Naming Convention

File name = Event ID



---

Status Lifecycle

Stage	Status

Generated	Ready (01)
Sent	Sending (02)



---

Sending Process

The system automatically processes events with: 👉 Status = Ready (01)

Steps:

1. Validate conditions


2. Check duplicate sending


3. Send TAR file


4. Update status to Sending




---

9. Idempotency (Duplicate Prevention)

Before sending data, the system checks if the same status was already sent.

Rules

If already ACK → Do not send

If already successfully sent → Do not send

If NACK → Retry allowed

If no record → Send


This ensures:

No duplicate transactions

Clean integration



---

10. Incoming Flow (ACK/NACK Handling)

After sending, Connexis processes the request and returns a response.

Processing Steps

1. Receive TAR file


2. Extract XML


3. Identify event using mo_event_id


4. Update database




---

ACK/NACK Mapping

Value	Meaning

01	ACK
02	NACK



---

Fix Implemented

Earlier:

NACK was incorrectly stored


Now:

Correctly stored as NACK



---

Error Handling

Error messages are logged

Stored for debugging



---

11. Retry Mechanism

Retry is allowed only when:

Status = NACK

No response received


Retry is blocked when:

Status = ACK

Already successfully sent



---

12. Closure Flow

